The Minister of Agriculture/ Natural Resources, Mr Sabo Nanono, Saturday in Calabar, lauded Governor Ben Ayade of Cross River State for initiating an agro-industrialisation policy  in the state. The minister called on governors of other  states to borrow a leaf from the governor. Nanono, who made the remarks shortly after visiting the ultra modern rice mill, Ogoja, cocoa processing factory, Ikom, rice seeds and seedlings factory, the feed mill company, the Calachika frozen factory, the noodles factory and the garment factory. The minister called  for increased budgetary allocation for the nation’s ailing research  institutes that are now moribund. In his remarks, the governor said the state under his watch was fully prepared to unlock whatever potentials available in the agriculture sector.